<subSubSection id="A030B9D79B99473295B94A14181072BA" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CE020EA723A439404C8A0C2C81DF73D8" pageNumber="663">
diagnosis An unusually large member of the 
<taxonomicName id="9EFFCCF26F397356F6F9445B024DFBA7" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group, similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0B1A9D239E728E78527BF8E5E9C8CFA5" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182057" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole napoensis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole napoensis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napoensis">napoensis</taxonomicName>
of Ecuador and more distantly so to 
<taxonomicName id="BDDED1840D45DC326A235F58A16602DA" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182062" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pepo Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pepo Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepo">pepo</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E7CF21498E7E6B669BCB662B53C7E05A" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182072" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundiceps">rotundiceps</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6D9381089CC01CBA6F7B243DC86FB5E2" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182081" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">sphaerica</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="6DD839830A8AF7B55A136F441AB2CFAA" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182082" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsphaerica">subsphaerica</taxonomicName>
, which are species variously from Colombia and Ecuador, and distinguished by the following set of traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="57089DEDFA3A3173C43C1A10351A3647" type="description">
<paragraph id="05B8027E271C9606EEA29BBE3A56FFC4" pageNumber="663">Major: promesonotum in side view forms a very large hump towering over the propodeum; from above the humeri are very broad, completely covering the rest of the pronotum below; from above the anterior margin of the postpetiolar node forms a perfect semicircle, with the posterior border a straight line forming its base; antennal scrobes absent; entire body covered by dense pilosity. measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 2.00, HL 2.06, SL 0.92, EL 0.22, PW 1.30. Paratype minor: HW 0.78, HL 0.82, SL 0.76, EL 0.14, PW 0.48. Color Major: body light reddish brown, appendages brownish yellow. Minor: concolorous light brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4E1D47AC87B45778C6520CC44AB44CE" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="48D8F49097B1F56D2CD9470D24EA0B14" pageNumber="663">
Range In addition to the type locality in Huila, 
<taxonomicName id="7E0DB4ABC23F2877CD8A058709E9B5BC" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182013" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole bellatrix Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole bellatrix Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellatrix">bellatrix</taxonomicName>
has been collected in Cundinamarca (1100 m), Magdalena (elevation unknown), and Meta (1000 m).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="448F1A17D0EB0BF72D7981303981CD08" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="31554519CCDFEDBABAAACF91440F2E16" pageNumber="663">Biology Winged queens were collected from the type nest sometime during 9-13 January.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
